#
# Format:  <name> <version> <sha256-of-extracted-binary>
#
# `scripts/install-scanners.sh` downloads each binary from its upstream
# release artifact, extracts the platform-specific archive, and verifies the
# SHA256 of the binary on disk against this file. In strict mode (default)
# any mismatch aborts; OPENSEC_SCANNER_VERIFY=warn lets local devs proceed
# after a manual rebuild.
#
# To refresh: download the upstream binary, run `shasum -a 256 bin/<name>`
# and copy the hex digest in here. Bump the version field at the same time.

